**  
**-1.** Design a **user-centric consent framework** requiring explicit opt-in for location sharing via clear, unavoidable prompts meeting GDPR/CCPA standards.  
**-2.** Develop **transparent real-time tracking** that lets users view/modify their exact shared coordinates through an in-app dashboard with audit logs.  
**-3.** Build **end-to-end encryption** for stored location data and enforce automatic deletion after 24 hours unless retention is explicitly authorized.  
**-4.** Integrate **OS-native privacy APIs** (e.g., iOS "Precise Location" toggle) and disable background processes unrelated to core app functions.  
**-5.** Publish open-source code snippets for independent verification of ethical data practices and submit the app for third-party security audits.

Example:**  
A safety-focused navigation app could:  
1) Show a pop-up: *“Share your precise location? [Allow] [Deny]”* with a link explaining how data is used;  
2) Let users set temporary “location masks” (e.g., approximate city-level sharing) via sliders;  
3) Encrypt GPS trails using AES-256 and auto-delete them post-journey;  
4) Partner with cybersecurity firms like Cure53 for annual penetration testing;  
5) Display a live map showing exactly what third parties (e.g., emergency services) receive.
